profile_positions.description:
UMF Training is a consulting company in a field of developing innovative training solutions and providing consultancy services to the private sector, governmental institutions, civil society organizations (CSOs) and international organizations. Our mission in one word is to INSPIRE, both people and organizations to achieve their potentials fully. Our team consist of international and local experts with profound knowledge gained by professional education and practical management experience in real business environment.
Main activities: 
•	Design and delivery of training workshops on various topics (Project Cycle Management, Training of Trainers, Business and Management Skills - Communication skills, Leadership, Presentation skills, etc.);
•	Facilitation and moderation of group events (workshops, seminars, conferences);
•	Team building);
•	Elaboration of local/regional strategies, studies, sector analysis etc.
•	Consulting and advisory services to management teams of SME, public institutions and civil society organizations;
•	Coaching;
•	Project development and implementation.

The USAID Strengthening Resource Mobilization Activity facilitates and fosters partnerships between the private sector, municipalities, and the local communities to promote local philanthropy, mobilize resources, and create an enabling environment for the local businesses. It assists partner LSGUs to engage with local communities and the private sector to plan local economic development initiatives. The overall objective of the assignment is to develop and implement a capacity building program to assist LAs, which have joined the M4EG Initiative, in elaborating LED plans in accordance with the principles and approaches outlined in the approved M4EG Concept. Main activities:
-	Delivering Capacity Building Program for the development of the local economic development plans (LEDPs);
-	Mentoring municipalities in the process of development of Local Economic Plans

The objective of the Local and Regional Competitiveness Project (LRCP) is to enhance the contribution of tourism to local economic development and improve the capacity of the Government and public entities to foster tourism growth and facilitate destination management. Responsible for:
-	Managing overall project activities;
-	Coordination of the project team and engaged experts;
-	Facilitation of stakeholders engagement in setting up Destination Management Organizations;
-	Participation at elaboration of tourism related documents;
-	Facilitation of destination management related workshops;
